ast_lead_provider\": \"openai\", \"task_count\": 9}))\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:79:- CypherClaw live command projects can layer quota-aware routing on top of those rules, redistributing work away from providers with degraded headroom and collapsing to single-agent mode when only one provider remains viable.\n++docs/startup-wizard.md:87:- In live CypherClaw homes, operator roadmap/status commands are also queue-backed where possible, so Telegram `/monitor`, `/prd`, and `/tasks` reflect the actual queue state and implementation order from `.sdp/state.db` instead of stale narrative summaries. Their totals count live executable tasks and exclude only split parents. `/monitor` also keeps `needs split` separate from `pending`, exposes queue-state drift if active task records and open run records disagree, and now includes compact `sdp-cli`-style gate/recent/provider lines. `/prd` distinguishes between stages that are truly absent, stages that are frozen, and stages that have only split-parent/decomposed work. `/tasks` defaults to the next actionable queue slices and supports focused backlog views like `/tasks pending 10`, `/tasks frozen`, `/tasks prd 6`, and `/tasks stage clone and home creation`.\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:12:import agent_selector\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:42:    def get_provider_status(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, object]]:\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:44:        for agent_name, provider in agent_selector.PROVIDERS.items():\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:45:            result[provider] = {\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:46:                \"status\": self.statuses.get(provider, \"healthy\"),\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:57:    def test_select_excludes_paused_provider(self, monkeypatch: pytest.MonkeyPatch, tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:58:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:63:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \"random\", lambda: 1.0)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:68:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:77:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \"random\", lambda: 1.0)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:86:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:91:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \"random\", lambda: 1.0)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:96:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:104:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \"random\", lambda: 1.0)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:105:        monkeypatch.setattr(selector, \"get_fitness\", lambda agent_name, category: 0.50)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:110:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:115:        monkeypatch.setattr(agent_selector.random, \"random\", lambda: 1.0)\n++tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py:120:        selector = agent_selector.AgentSelector(\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:184:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:262:- `grep -r \"anthropic\\\\|openai\\\\|gemini\\\\|claude\" /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/ --include=\"*.py\" -l` showed provider-aware code in:\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:268:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:275:  - `agent_selector = AgentSelector(observatory=observatory, state_file=...)`\n++docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:338:  - `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/agent_selector.py` (`6.9K`)\n++docs/coherence-foundations.md:184:When a system uses multiple LLM providers (Claude, GPT, Gemini, local models), each with different capabilities and failure modes, governance rules cannot be embedded in any single model's system prompt. They must be externalized into infrastructure that evaluates all models' outputs uniformly. PromptClaw's constitution is model-agnostic: it evaluates text output regardless of which agent or model produced it.\n++docs/command-reference.md:90:In CypherClaw live command deployments, `run` can also honor `sdp-cli` quota telemetry. Healthy and warn providers stay eligible for routing, degraded providers stop receiving new work, and full exhaustion falls back to the provider with the best remaining headroom so runs continue in degraded mode.\n++docs/command-reference.md:174:- `/quota` shows provider headroom, active agents, and exclusions from quota-aware routing.\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:218:### 2.1 Modify agent_selector.py\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:220:Add Ollama to the provider map and fitness scores:\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:223:# In agent_selector.py\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:225:PROVIDERS = {\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:257:# In quota_monitor.py, in _load_provider_headroom() or get_agent_headroom()\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:260:    provider = PROVIDERS.get(agent)\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:261:    if provider == \"local\":\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:286:    category = agent_selector.detect_category(task_label or prompt[:200])\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:734:Once you've validated that Ollama produces acceptable results, increase its fitness scores to make it the default choice:\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:737:# In agent_selector.py, raise ollama scores above cloud agents:\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:771:If Ollama is down, the agent selector naturally falls back to cloud agents (they have the next-highest fitness scores and full quota).\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:800:| 4 | Apply code changes (agent_selector, daemon, quota_monitor) | Day 10 | Step 3 |\n++docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:805:| 9 | Monitor, tune fitness scores | Day 11+ | Production traffic |\n++docs/architecture.md:54:- when a live provider should be deprioritized or excluded because quota headroom is degraded\n++docs/architecture.md:87:In CypherClaw-style live command deployments, command routing can consult `sdp-cli` quota telemetry. Healthy and warn providers remain eligible, degraded and paused providers are excluded from new work, and if every provider is degraded the runtime falls back to the provider with the most remaining headroom instead of refusing to operate.\n++docs/architecture.md:115:Operator-facing Telegram status now also splits cleanly between built-ins and routed work. Queue-backed commands like `/monitor`, `/quota`, `/prd`, and `/tasks` read live runtime state directly instead of relying on conversational summaries, so queue progress, roadmap status, provider health, and actionable worklists stay aligned with the SQLite authority DB. Queue totals use one canonical denominator everywhere: all live executable tasks, excluding only split parents. `/prd` now also distinguishes empty roadmap stages from frozen or decomposed ones: stages with only frozen work are shown as `frozen`, stages with only split parents are shown as `decomposed`, and only truly absent work is shown as `not loaded`. `/monitor` now carries a compact `sdp-cli`-style status slice too: completion-gate status, latest completed run verdict/pair, and per-agent quota/provider health, while still surfacing queue-state drift when the active-task and open-task-run records disagree. `/tasks` now defaults to an operator-first queue view with running work, next root tasks, split-needed work, and attention items, while filtered slices like `/tasks frozen` or `/tasks all 20` expose deeper backlog details on demand. Roadmap-aware task slices such as `/tasks prd 6` and `/tasks stage clone and home creation` resolve through the same roadmap/batch files as `/prd`, so stage-level work inspection stays aligned with the live execution spine.\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:1:\"\"\"Tests for daemon fallback when agent providers degrade.\"\"\"\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:36:    def get_provider_status(self) -> dict[str, dict[str, object]]:\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:40:        provider = cypherclaw_daemon.PROVIDERS[agent_name]\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:41:        return float(self.status[provider][\"headroom\"])\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:43:    def force_status(self, provider: str, status: str, **_: object) -> None:\n++tests/test_daemon_fallback.py:44:        self.status.setdefault(provider, {})\n++tests/test_daemoassert \\\"Restart=on-failure\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"ConditionPathExists=/home/user/.local/bin/sdp-cli\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"Environment=PATH=/home/user/.local/bin:/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"Environment=PYTHONPATH=/home/user/sdp-cli/src\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"Restart=always\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"RestartPreventExitStatus=75\\\" in runner_unit\\n+    assert \\\"SuccessExitStatus=75\\\" in runner_unit\\n \\n \\n def test_boot_hardening_no_longer_restores_state_or_starts_runner_directly() -> None:\\ndiff --git a/tests/test_room_listener_runtime.py b/tests/test_room_listener_runtime.py\\nindex fb7e02e..115b5ef 100644\\n--- a/tests/test_room_listener_runtime.py\\n+++ b/tests/test_room_listener_runtime.py\\n@@ -4,12 +4,20 @@ from __future__ import annotations\\n import math\\n import os\\n import random\\n+import subprocess\\n import sys\\n \\n \\n sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \\\"..\\\", \\\"my-claw\\\", \\\"tools\\\"))\\n \\n-from room_listener import is_hallucination\\n+import room_listener\\n+from room_listener import (\\n+    capture_audio,\\n+    is_hallucination,\\n+    resolve_jack_capture_ports,\\n+    resolve_pipewire_target,\\n+    se